prompt:
Implement `parse_markup(text: str) -> dict` that parses a simple markup format.

Markup patterns:
- `**text**` → {'type': 'bold', 'content': 'text'}
- `[[link]]` → {'type': 'link', 'content': 'link'}
- `{{cite}}`  → {'type': 'cite', 'content': 'cite'}

Return a dict:
{'segments': [...], 'errors': [{'position': int, 'description': str}, ...]}

Malformed cases to handle:
- Unclosed `**` — produce a segment of type 'text' up to the unclosed marker.
- Nested markers inside each other (e.g., `**[[text]]**`) — keep outer, convert inner to plain text within the outer.
- Empty markers (`****`, `[[]]`) — produce an error but still include an empty segment.
- Markers split across lines — treat as invalid, produce error.
- Regular text with no markers — single text segment, no errors.
